The paper deals with the problem of coalitional manipulation in voting systems, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of algorithms and approximation techniques suggests that it could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of linear programming and efficient separation oracles, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
